cs.SI, cs.SOC, cs.IR, cs.DB, cs.CL 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper focuses on using a social network (Twitter) to estimate users' home locations, which falls under the scope of social and information networks. 
2. cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences) - The paper analyzes the behavior of users on social media (Twitter) and how their relationships can be used to estimate home locations. 
3. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) - The paper involves retrieving information (home locations) from social media data (Twitter) using network-based methods. 
4. cs.DB (Databases) - The paper involves managing and analyzing large amounts of data (Twitter data) to estimate home locations. 
5. cs.CL (Computation and Language) - The paper may involve natural language processing techniques to extract location information from user profiles or tweets on Twitter.
